      <procstep>
        <procdesc>The Bailey Equal-Area Grid data set was mathematically generated by ESRI according to the methodology described in the article, "A Grid Formed of Meridians and Parallels for the Comparison and Measurement of Area" by Dr. Harry P. Bailey.

The area of the grid cells was calculated by using the mean area of the 'core' grid cells (i.e., those not adjoining 180 degrees longitude).  The data were in the Equal-Area Cylindrical projection in meters using the Clarke 1866 spheroid.  The cells bordering the extreme longitudes are actually slightly smaller in longitudinal extent than the other cells because of a limit in the algorithm used to generate them.  These smaller cells were not included in the calculation of mean cell area.  The value of mean cell area was then assigned to the area attributes for all cells in the grid.</procdesc>
